<img src="https://i2.wp.com/saharareporters.com/sites/default/files/NARD-President-Dr-Aliyu-Sokomba.jpg" alt="Aliyu Sokomba" data-recalc-dims="1"/> After days of strike action, the National Association of Resident Doctors has called off the decision with effect from Monday, June 22, 2020. The announcement was made through a communique read to journalists by Dr Aliyu Sokomba, President of the group, on Sunday in Abuja after its National Executive Council meeting.   	 		 	<img src="https://i1.wp.com/saharareporters.com/sites/default/files/styles/normal_medium/public/NARD-President-Dr-Aliyu-Sokomba.jpg" data-recalc-dims="1"/>Aliyu Sokomba The doctors are agitating for more welfare package from government in light of agreement reached in the past. PUBLIC HEALTH  News    AddThis  :       Original Author  :   Saharareporters, New York     Disable advertisements  :Original Article